meg remy's 6th album under her u.s girls moniker is by far the most fully realised, and it's timing in 2018 was impeccable, given that many of the songs on it addressed the abuse of white male power; a subject that of course got catapulted into the mainstream consciousness after the harvey weinstein scandal and the subsequent #metoo movement. but what makes such songs extraordinary here, is the fact that the dark lyrics are coupled to uptempo pop arrangements that recall the likes of kylie, blondie, nate dogg and abba in pretty equal measure. upon first listen, the single 'pearly gates' sounds like a delicious slice of retro g-funk, but listen closer and you'll catch lyrics detailing how st peter will only let women into heaven who are prepared to sleep with him. â €
.â €

text:
the me too movement was silent in senegal. these women are trying to change that

late last year, as #metoo spread from social media feeds in the united states, intensifying into a slew of global hashtags -- #balancetonporc, #yotambien, and #quellavoltache among them -- two women in the senegalese capital of dakar decided to start a movement of their own: #nopiwouma.

translated from wolof into english, it means, "i will not shut up." but it's been difficult getting women to speak out. "nopiwouma was never going to work like me too, because in senegalese culture it's hard for us to even get people to talk about it," senegalese blogger ndambaw kama (nk) thiat, who co-founded the movement with tech entrepreneur olivia codou, told cnn.read more o @cnn

text: salute to ricardo cruz, eic of gq brasil, who is off to new adventures after 8 years piloting the brand. this is one of his four march 2018 covers ( swipe for the other three). it was a special issue dedicated to women with a guest editor - the writer/screenwriter/activist antonia pellegrino. the four cover stars are well-known, well-respected actresses. the idea was sparked by a talk fiona hayes, art director of condÃ© nast international, gave at a gq editorsâ€™ conference in paris back in january. hayes took a hard look at the way menâ€™s magazines needed to adjust to the world post harvey weinstein and #metoo.  the cover # reads:â€™the responsibility belongs to everyone.â€™ the photography is by cassia tabatini and the art director carolina goulart. this was a major statement then in a macho country like brasil. @pellegrino.antonia @brunalinzmeyer @danielafalcao1 @ricardofrancacruzz @caiapitanga @brunalinzmeyer @leandraleal @taisdeverdade @gqbrasil @cassiatabatinistudio @theartdictator #photography #magazinedesign #magazinecover #gqbrasil

text:
every human being on the planet wants to be happy. 
anything that anyone desires is because they think their desire will make them happy. 
whether it is health, money, a loving relationship, material things, accomplishments, a job, or anything at all, the desire for happiness is the bottom line of all of them. 
but remember that happiness is a state inside of us, and something on the outside can only bring fleeting happiness, because material things are impermanent.

text:
on december 18th 2018, athena hosted a #metoo adolescent girls and young women town hall in nairobi, kenya. the town hall was an interactive dialogue focused on sexual harassment, safety and survival. the session created an open platform for young women to discuss and explore the roles of gender inequity, religion, cultural norms, poverty and lack of access to education in exacerbating young womenâ€™s vulnerability to sexual harassment, violence and exploitation.

young women shared examples of lived experiences and community trends and were invited to unpack and explore what safety looks like in the workplace and beyond. additionally, young women offered practical ideas and solutions to promote gender transformation, safe societies for women and girls and tips to eliminate sexual harassment. â€œwe continue to talk about creating safe spaces here or there like churches or schools or our homes. we need a change that creates a safe world. it shouldn't just be some spaces that are safe" participant â€œsexual harassment is when a no, no longer means no!â€ #whatgirlswant leader â€œwhen women talk about assault, no one is willing to step forward and support you and take your hand. the law enforcement comes into question. can the law and the judiciary act system actually support women to have rights and control of their sexuality? men dominate so many spaces. men feel that they are in more powerful positions.â€ #whatgirlswant champion â€œsilence is a driver of sexual harassment.  if you see something do you speak or become mute? do you say it's none of my business when something happens? gang rape has become normalized and accepted in our communities. when you see it happening around you, speak against it, even if itâ€™s only a small act.â€ positive women voices 
#whatwomenwant #whatgirlswant #metoo

text:
hot news
sonu nigam gegerkan media dengan pernyataannya yang meledak ğŸ˜¯

penyanyi sonu nigam menghadapi waktu yang sangat sulit ketika ia meminta larangan penggunaan pengeras suara di tempat-tempat keagamaan. jumlah ancaman yang terus-menerus dia hadapi semuanya. sekarang, setelah setahun, dia sekali lagi membuat pernyataan yang sangat kontroversial. 
pada pertemuan agenda aaj tak, penyanyi playback ini mengambil penggalian pada pujian yang dinikmati penyanyi dari pakistan di negara india. media melaporkan dari apa yang sonu nigam ungkapkan, â€œkadang-kadang, saya merasa seolah-olah akan lebih baik jika saya berasal dari pakistan. setidaknya saya akan mendapat tawaran dari indiaâ€ 
sonu lebih lanjut mengkritik budaya remix di industri musik india, dan berkata, â€œsaat ini, penyanyi harus membayar perusahaan musik untuk pertunjukannya. jika kita tidak mengeluarkan uang, mereka akan memainkan lagu yang dinyanyikan oleh penyanyi lain dan menyorotnya. kemudian, mereka akan mengambil uang dari merekaâ€. sonu bahkan berbicara tentang bagaimana penyanyi asal pakistan, atif aslam, teman dekatnya atau bahkan rahat fateh ali khan tidak diminta untuk membayar untuk menyanyi di sebuah acara.

lebih lanjut, dia berbicara tentang gelombang #metoo yang telah memukul industri bollywood akhir-akhir ini. sonu nigam berkata, â€œsaya belum punya cukup kesempatan untuk berbicara tentang hal ini. saya sendiri adalah saksi bagaimana kekuasaan disalahgunakan. saya berkata #metoo sepuluh tahun yang lalu, ketika seorang wartawan terus mengganggu saya. dia telah memberi tahu seorang direktur bahwa jika direktur tersebut bekerja dengan saya, maka wartawan tersebut akan bunuh diri". sonu menyesali kurangnya bukti dan menambahkan. ğŸ˜¯

a lot has happened since september 25. @iamtanushreeduttaofficialâ€™s brutally truthful television interview about actor #nanapatekarâ€™s sexual misconduct, followed by mahima kukrejaâ€™s (@agirlofherwords) outing of comedian #utsavchakraborty as a serial harasser a few weeks later, unleashed a turbo-charged outflowing of similar stories from other working women, and new reports are still trickling in. the rot of toxic masculinity has been exposed, and the corroded spirits of countless survivors lie bare before a population of slack-jawed bystandersâ€¦now what?

this is a question that we at verve asked ourselves while curating a thought-provoking collection of articles in our november-december issue, which examines a few important aspects of this ongoing and multidimensional conversation. click on the link in bio for some insightful perspectives from an inspiring group of contributors: @zubaanbooks, @aishwaryaarumbakkam, @shalswrit, #rutujashinde, @taraanandart and @opashona.

text_retweet:
feminism is light coming to confront the darkness.
it is a coming of change and a warning to those who are not willing to let this change build a new world.
feminism is art and action, history and future.
feminism is present. a gift built to new heights with the fire of each new generation.
feminism is anger and love, ambition and patience.
feminism is sacrificial and giving. a fulfilment of what is right in a world that asks it to pay a heavy price.
feminism is the man who fights against the worst versions of himself. he takes the time to uplift a woman where once his predecessors pushed her down.
feminism is the man who loves his daughter unconditionally, is the man who protects his sister unquestioningly, and worships his mother eternally.
feminism is the right to choose in a world that gives her opportunities of choice in a society that does not make her pay a heavier price for the choices she makes.
feminism is not the gains of the white woman at the expense of the brown womanâ€™s voice.
feminism is not a t-shirt that celebrates feminism at the cost of a childâ€™s humanity in a sweatshop factory.
feminism is not apologetic. so the statement â€œiâ€™m sorryâ€ does not apply.
feminism is bold and brash, calm and thoughtful.
feminism is black and brown, powerful and resilient.
feminism is poetry and practicality.
feminism is ancestral and prophetic.
.

text:
some recaps from the november issue of the caravan magazine (@thecaravanmagazine ).
worked with the brilliant samia singh (@samiasingh_art ) who illustrated the opener for nikita saxena's piece on accusations of sexual harassment against news anchor gaurav sawant. the piece sheds light on the gender bias in the  journalism and media, particularly the defense beat, which is what sawant was on. this was part of the caravan's special issue titled 'the reckoning' carrying reports of sexual harassment faced by women in the entertainment, media and arts industry. 
one of the toughest, but also most satisfying issues to work on, primarily to break the legacy of problematic visuals that accompany stories on sexual harassment and abuse. 
#metoo #thecaravanmagazine #printisnotdead #thereckoning #gauravsawant #journalism #editorialillustration #gender

text:
recognising sexual harassment at the workplace:
harassment occurs in the most unexpected way. it starts with moves that appear to be innocent but ends up in unprofessional and inappropriate behaviour. anything that appears to be sexual, unpleasant and inappropriate, which may or may not be within your tolerance limits, amounts to sexual harassment.

launchbox aims to provide a safe co-working space for not only females but males too as this can happen to anyone. the first step is acknowledging that this can happen and how to deal with it accordingly.

text:
when we get braver we start to remember.

we're faced with a quandry then..... do we tell our tory to give our inner child freedom or do we maintain our silence and give our past even more power over us?

what ever your answer you are welcome in our group #speakoutsisterhood
 check it out 
https://www.facebook.com/groups/805644186440105/

we all have a right to speak out, our experience is nothing to be ashamed of.

#endviolenceagainstwomenandgirls

text:
for years, i suffered from deep depression. iâ€™ve been through so much, and i always wondered â€œwhy meâ€. you name it, iâ€™ve been through it, heartbreak, suicidal thoughts, financial downfall, postpartum, death of a parent, death period, situations i thought i would never get out, etc. but today i can say, god put me through those things because he knew that i was strong enough to get through it. not only that, he knew i would use what the devil meant for bad, and i would turn it into something good. 
about 4 years ago, i was ready to give up on life, i had it! i felt like the world was pure evil, until  a stranger changed my life forever. all they did was paid my toll of $1.50, but it was on a day where i just had enough. but that kind gesture which was probably nothing to them meant so much to me. it made me realize there are still kind people out there and that through spreading love we can change the world.

thatâ€™s were i founded my up and coming non profit, â€œthe power of a dollarâ€, itâ€™s not about money but itâ€™s about being kind and spreading love wherever you can. a simple smile or a thank you can change someoneâ€™s day or life. you never know what the person next to you is going through but if we are open to being kind and spreading love just imagine how beautiful this world can be.

this year i decided to give back to the homeless in newark, we will be making gift bags filled with essentials. if you are interested in helping out or donating let me know. hereâ€™s some donations we have already received, i also wanted to get the kids involved so we talked about why itâ€™s important to be kind and decorated the bags â˜ºï¸#giveback #spreadlove #godislove #bekind #fundraiser #donate #changetheworld #bethechange #metoo #thepoad

text:
i love my blonde hair. when i finally got it to the color i wanted, i was ecstatic. i was so happy that before we got married i made nathan agree that unless we were in poverty, that was the one item of discretionary spending i could always haveâ€”my salon trips every few months. itâ€™s not about just the vanity, but also about the time i get to spend relaxing and caring for myself. .
i scheduled my appointment with the color and cut consultant tonight and i didnâ€™t actually tell her in advance what i wanted. why? because i was so tired of being â€œthat girl from the newsâ€ that i actually was considering getting rid of the hair i loved so much i wanted in it a prenuptial agreement. i wanted to be someone other than me. .
i got mad at myself when i got there. i love my blonde hairâ€”i love it even though the man who hurt me made creepy comments when i colored it that way. i love it even though images of me with it have become synonymous with a letter i wrote that dared call out injustice. .
itâ€™s just my hair, sure. but i love it. and i wanted to give it up to be someone else today, because iâ€™m hurting that much.
.
but, hereâ€™s to hurting and living anyway. hereâ€™s to being proud of my blonde, loud, unashamed self even when itâ€™s hard. and hereâ€™s to a stylist who let me cry for a few minutes in her chair tonight because i really needed a therapist and could only get a hair appointment. ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ğŸ˜‚ #metoo #timesup #goodstylist #selfcare #weekfromhell #itsokaytocry #victimsarepeopletoo #thankyou

text:
this year broke my heart, mended it like i never could imagine, and taught me so much about what is important in life. self reflection, your experiences, the people who choose to be in your life, and the environment you choose to put yourself in. those who cannot see that about life, or are just simply not in that place, cannot see the beauty in it. iâ€™m understanding that now and iâ€™m so thankful for every â€œbadâ€ thing that happened this year. turns out, all of it, was some of the best things that could have happened to me. i feel fearless and so much stronger for it all. 
with that said, i am free!!! turned in my old apartment keys today and iâ€™m on the road to my first real home on my own as an adult. itâ€™s truly an incredible feeling and accomplishment. thank you to everyone who has been by my side this past year and that could see my path, long before i could. i am so lucky to have friends who support their friends fully, and self evaluate! itâ€™s so much nicer (and healthy) to face the demons you have head on, and work on bettering you, in a nourishing and patient way. i kept so much in for so long, and it feels so good to be honest about it and grow from that experience. chapter 30 is a month and some change away...iâ€™m ready for it! and finally being able to speak the truth about my experiences and my journey. you donâ€™t have to be unhappy every day, you donâ€™t have to give up who you are for someone or something. and you donâ€™t have hold onto negativity in your heart for those who disappoint you. my path is clear and i am so happy to have every single one of my â€œpersonsâ€ on the journey with me. clarity for the first time in years, is such a beautiful thing. i love you all & iâ€™m excited for this new chapter!!! ğŸ’ƒğŸ½ğŸ’ƒğŸ½

text:
hey, i'm sorry yall for being gone so much lately. it's been a wild ride. here's a small update:
1. i'm going to have gender affirmation surgery on feburary 7th.
2. i'm currently going through a huge shift in therapy, and its extremely overwhelming. we are working hard because we think we found the answer of what's been going on in my life, once i have all my ducks in a row, i will definitely share.
3. tomorrow is my last therapy session for 2 weeks, because my therapists office is closed, this time of the year is awful for me, because so much changes with therapy. many therapy offices close, and i go from 4-5 hours of intense community based therapy, to none. 
4. i'm figuring our health issues, and it's really overwhelming at this time. i'm in the middle of a flare, and its not helping me. i'm dizzy, lightheaded, and nauseous, (but thankfully sucking on menthol cough drops stops my cough drops, and it helps my partner as well) my pots has gotten worse, and i'm thankful my pain as been pretty low, except some excess joint swelling!! 5. i'm starting with a therapist who specialized in dissociative identity disorder, and i'm hoping with collaboration from my current therapist (and the one i'll continue to work with) it will help organize some of that. 
6. i'm becoming more confident being me, and counting down the days until surgery!!! -----
thank you all so much, and i love that you have continued with me down this journey of self discovery!

text:
last year (and previous years) but last year could of took me out. i struggled tremendously with my mind. i may have shared some darker stuff that warranted a few people to reach out but i would never express the whole picture and many never noticed. i was in such a dark place. i made a anonymous instagram to vent. to get stuff out but i was too ashamed to do it as me. so these are post from last year.  i know not many will read all this. but maybe there is just 1 person. that can't tell their story so i'm sharing mine to let you know you're not alone. hang on! 
i often thought of ways i could take myself out.  thinking of my kids of course helped a great deal because i didn't want to pass them the pain,  but i didn't think i was good enough for them anyway... anywho i didn't know if i believed in anything anymore but i do know i seeked god with all i had left, after straying away so far.

the lord is with you when you are with him. if you seek him, he will be found by you, but if you forsake him, he will forsake you. . and i have no immediate story. i still had to fight! and fight! and fall! and fight some more staying faithful and not straying away. still fighting. it's been a long challenging year but i can say i'm ending this year on a much more positive note.  people are hurting out there!! because of someone else's story gave me some strength. i'll add another story to the mix. 
#letstalkaboutit #breakthestigma

text:
recently someone asked me , nirav ! do signature analysis really work ?

does it helps people in education sectors too ?

the person was itself from education sector .

when i says yes , she ask me live case study in education segment which i solved up through signature analysis , a case come from north india city .

a school going teen aged around 12 year old ( say named as vikas - name change for privacy purpose ) was been hesitating to go to school.

they consult to counsellor and after 3-4 session , the counsellor was not able to sort out the reason of child avoiding to go to school.

then parent approach to one senior professional counsellor.

after 2 session counselling with vikas , even senior counsellor does not came up with conclusion.

finally on recommendation they approach me .

when i look upon the handwriting sample , 1st thing i felt reason was fear of studying , but the reason was different  hence i ask parents to give me signature of child.

when i saw the signature of vikas , bang on , i found something fishy.

it show me fear of sexual molestation at sub conscious level.

i reply to the parent of vikas as , does he is scare of any specific person in house or relative or in school , further get to know the school is good at teaching and they teach childrens with extreme care , there is no chance that child is abuse or shout upon by teachers or staff or even by parents.

i keep insisting parents to further inquire as the signature sample show me abusing traits.

hence on my request , parent take vikas to professional counsellor and when further inquire , the result was shocking.

child was scare to go to school because he was been molested at school.

signature analysis is an amazing science which opens up the secrets of human brain.

to learn about this amazing science then book your seat for 5th and 6 th jan 2018 - signature analysis mastery course - an 16 hours power pack session by nirav hiingu .

text:
shady
.

see what i really think happened? so when you take a medical leave they *absolutely can't fire you by law*, but when i returned to random house my editor had been fired, and both my imprint and my editor had changed. because meg newman is a klansmen, she likely hated my book, and didn't want to keep me on, which was evidenced by my having to hunt her down and her giving me the cold shoulder until my agent offered to step in. i just let it slide and tried *one more time*, when she just pushed me off to another editor ...a junior editor who *can't* work alone
.

subsequently, together they approved *every single one of my narrative evolutions*, but refused to engage the text beyond the outline i submitted with chunks of writing
.

all they would say is, "sounds so interest! bye!" knowing i had not only requested help but kept saying, "we can discuss this at length!" still nothing
.

then i got hacked and they saw the real out
.

bc they thought all my emails had been erased they returned my *very long memoir* back to me in less then two weeks, without having fact checked (i was given an extra month for both the reference and recipes) saying "it was nothing like the original contract"
.

well... i got my emails back, you bunch of old bitches and they are *legally binding*
.

plus, i don't think they like the fact that hillary clinton is donald trump, bc she's their cover, and also they hated me bc i think the #metoo movement is disorganized as all fuck, so not only did they deliberately discriminate against my disability (if you have a person off medical leave u essentially have to do what they say if it won't cause "undo harm" to the company; me asking them to do their job, which is *reading*, seems reasonable) but also circumstancally? avery books hasn't published one black author in years! and they said the book was *only* rejected bc i spoke about the "draw backs of american health care" ( -- about black people, gays, trans, muslims, etc. so that is at once race, gender, sex and religious discrimination.. all whic had been *approved*) but since they thought my emails were gone, i couldnt retrieve them and they could hold me to my original contract
.

.
.
this is my sister.  sheâ€™s completely different from me and by different i mean we couldnâ€™t be more polar opposite.  sheâ€™s incredibly smart, professional, practices law, organized, assertive, and a natural leader.  she takes charge, doesnâ€™t mess around, and gets things done.  sheâ€™s also an incredible mom, a very dope sister, and has grown up to be a staple and safe space for our family.  maybe i love her a lot.  but maybe i didnâ€™t always like her.
.
.

text:
sometimes when i can't sleep at night 
i hear his laugh
i see his smirk
his need to conquer,  to coerce, envelope me, entangle me
renders me helpless

text:
i used to think that the only way to connect with other strong women was to find a support group or attend a networking event. neither appealed to me. so i stayed in my comfort zone, and rarely made the effort to meet new people. what i failed to realize at the time is that the internet offers global connectivity from the comfort of your couch. iâ€™ve found amazing, inspiring, and brave women by simply following the hashtag #womensupportingwomen ğŸ’•
.
.
iâ€™ve found a selfless girl gang community who fights for the rights of sisters and daughters and mothers and strangers across the globe. just when you lose faith in humanity, the light shines through.ğŸ’¡ğŸ‘­ğŸ‘­
.
.
join your local girl gang. find your tribe. build it. learn from the stories of other strong women. spend your precious time with those who inspire you and empower you. surround yourself with people who operate at a higher vibration... the ones smarter than you, stronger than you, happier than you. learn from them. observe their habits. study their consistencies. ğŸ““
.
.
you are the average of the 5 people you spend the most time with. will you love yourself enough to place a high standard on your time, energy, and attention?
.
.
avoid those who spend your time gossiping. avoid those who are jealous. avoid materialistic topics and people. pay attention to what is influencing you & feeding your brain. do not allow the misery of others to become a parasite that you carry the burden for. you are worthy of more.
.
.
we all have a voice. use whatever platform you have (no matter how big or small) to tell your story and positively improve the lives of others. connect with a community of givers. understand the rich abundance of giving back and believe in that the universe will bring that same goodness back to you. ğŸŒğŸŒ™âœ¨
.
.

text:
find what makes you happy. follow your joy. worrying about what others are doing is pointless. .
love yourself. understand your journey is yours alone. your job is not to please anyone, just like it's nobody's job to make you happy. .
if you are worrying about what another is doing, you are giving them power over your emotions. the power lies within you.
.
be mindful of where you focus your attention. we are the only ones who can truly make ourselves happy. that is by following what makes you feel alive!

text:
tw: rape, sexual assault
christa hayburn was sexually assaulted by a superior at the police department where she served as a law enforcement officer.

for the next two years she did not report the assault to the department for fear of losing her job. when she experienced an unrelated injury and found out that she could no longer work as a police officer, she finally felt that she could report the assault to the internal affairs department. after turning in a written description of the assault, she was taken to an interrogation room and questioned by two detectives for 6-8 hours. â€œthey whisked me away as soon as they saw that this involved a person in a position of power. that day was very retraumatizing.â€ christa says the department and the city did not take her report seriously or take measures to ensure that the perpetrator could not sexually assault others. after filing her report, christa faced retaliation from the city. they expressed doubt about christaâ€™s medical reports regarding the injury that prevented her from continuing to serve on the police force, and appointed a private investigator to follow her.
over the next four years, christa fought against city officials to make sure that her report of sexual assault was investigated appropriately and that her injury was taken seriously. she eventually resigned from the department. later, two more women reported being sexually assaulted by the same perpetrator, who had been promoted to deputy inspector.

christa filed a federal retaliation lawsuit against the city, entering an extended legal process. she ultimately decided to discontinue the case for the good of herself and her family. â€œthe day before my deposition i read through my internal affairs report and saw all the transcripts attacking me and attacking my credibility...trying to find flaws in me and my story,â€ says christa. â€œi thought to myselfâ€”iâ€™m done. how much more can i put myself through? when do i say, â€˜enough is enough? thatâ€™s when i started a journey of setting boundaries for myself.â€™â€
#25daysofsweaters #metoo

text:
feels like a dream. did that really happen or was it all some strange, exhilarating, in the moment/out of body experience? 
this role of vixen in the eight was such an honor to step into, and a huge responsibility. like our gifted director @rycardo1980 has said, at first glance the reindeer monologues might look like a whimsical satire about santaâ€™s talking herd, but inevitably the audience bore witness to something much more powerful - a timely and relevant statement about the times we live in. 
how do we perceive the stories of survivors in the era of the #metoo movement? who do we believe when women come forward against men who abuse their power without fear of consequence? what needs to change so that this sort of thing doesnâ€™t happen anymore? (...and why do we insist on telling children that itâ€™s okay for a mysterious powerful white man to surveil and punitively judge their character while allowing that fictional stranger to break into their home in the middle of the night â€” because itâ€™s just one night out of the year and he leaves presents?! donâ€™t worry though, i wonâ€™t be going around telling anyoneâ€™s children the truth about santa ğŸ˜) vixen represented each and every woman whose story of abuse and assault has ever been questioned. vixen could have been anita hill or dr. christine blasey ford, and every victim of rape, abuse and sexual harassment made to feel at fault for the wrongdoing against them by the hands of delusional and entitled sex criminals. 
it was a challenging role, one that asked me to leave it all on the stage and hold nothing back. iâ€™m so grateful for the opportunity to have been part of this important, moving and brilliantly crafted production. 
experiences like this instill in me that the pursuit of acting is one that can truly open minds and hearts ... and that vulnerability will always be the greatest source of strength. 
with love, vixen â¤ï¸
.
.
.

text:
fort lauderdale, fla. â€” former trump campaign adviser roger stone has settled a $100 million lawsuit accusing him of publishing lies on the far-right infowars website.

the wall street journal reports exiled chinese businessman guo wengui sued stone in march, saying stone accused him of being a â€œturncoat criminalâ€ who violated u.s. election law. stone now says his conduct was â€œirresponsible.â€ guo has criticized high-level corruption in china and applied for asylum in the u.s.

the settlement reached monday identifies chinese-american media tycoon bruno wu and a former trump staffer as the sources of false information.

the settlement allows stone to avoid paying any damages if he publishes national newspaper ads apologizing for the statements and retracts the statements online. he still is of interest to investigators probing russian interference in the 2016 election.

text:
in this house we take a lot a lot a lot of selfies. we take selfies of us in places that represent things that might not mean a lot to other people but that mean the world to us and hereâ€™s why...â€¢
â€¢
in this house we do hard things. sometimes multiple times a day. we challenge each other to do more, say more, be more and show up when it would be a lot easier to hide or just stay in.â€¢
â€¢
today we visited the doctor and after three full months of a new dose of the anxiety meds the three of us together, but mostly joel, determined this was the best dose yet. 
he feels strong. 
he feels in control. 
he feels capable. 
he feels safe. 
he feels listened to. 
he feels heard. 
he feels. 
and that in itself is an absolute gift and 100% selfie worthy in my book.â€¢
â€¢
i will encourage and take selfies in this family for-ever. i want my kids to roll their eyes but always know that every documentation of a milestone doesnâ€™t end when they are independent. i want them to celebrate the small and huge things forever. i want them to know that life is hard and beautiful with everything in between and that while i was around i was by their side to cheer them on and document their strength so that next time they remember last time and know they are capable.â€¢
â€¢
take the selfies. 
document all the things. 
we do this life only one time that we know of. 
share the everything out of it.

did you know that it is not necessary to have total amnesia for the actions of alter personalities in dissociative identity disorder?

1) gaps in memory of significant life events (e.g., periods of childhood or adolescence; the death of a grandparent, getting married, giving birth); 2) lapses in dependable memory (e.g., of what happened today, of well-leamed skills such as how to do their job, use a computer, read, drive); and

text: iâ€™m a feminist, iâ€™ve always been, since i started noticing how our world is flooded with crap that discriminates women. that was a long time ago, and is still happening...everywhere, at school, at bars, festivals, when you go to college, on tv,...some things might have mutated (not really changed) but they are still there. instead of a comedian laughing at how women are beaten at home, now we have denigrating programs like â€˜the housewives of xxxâ€™ where stereotypes of women (created by men) insult each other and fight over their machos...or we constantly listen to singers who talk about â€˜their womenâ€™ as if they were sexual toys...and this is the top of the iceberg...the number of women who are sexually assaulted a year is scary, the number of women who are psychologically, physically or sexually abused a year is scary, the number of women whose genitalia is mutilated a year is scary, the number of women who are killed by their partners a year is scary...and the list goes on and on and on...really? so yes, iâ€™m a feminist. we all should be feminists because obviously (and sadly) there are lots of things that need to be changed still to live in a world where there is gender equality and women are not discriminated against. #noalaviolenciamachista #stopviolenceagainstwomen #yotambien #metoo #timeisup #genderequality

text:
anxiety can occur when a person fears that something bad is going to happen. it is a non-medical term that refers to a feeling of fear or worry that often relates to a particular issue or concern.

anxiety has been linked to stress. as well as feelings of fear and worry, it often involves physical symptoms, such as muscle tension.

it is different from a panic attack, which is a symptom of panic disorder. anxiety often relates to a specific event or situation, although this is not always the case.

a panic attack, meanwhile, can happen without any specifiable trigger, and the symptoms are far more severe than the symptoms of anxiety.

however, if levels of stress and anxiety continue for a long time, further problems may develop. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2018/12/17/how-to-recognize-an-anxiety-attack/ #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #therapydog #trauma #doitfordolly

anxiety has been linked to stress. as well as feelings of fear and worry, it often involves physical symptoms, such as muscle tension.

it is different from a panic attack, which is a symptom of panic disorder. anxiety often relates to a specific event or situation, although this is not always the case.

a panic attack, meanwhile, can happen without any specifiable trigger, and the symptoms are far more severe than the symptoms of anxiety.

however, if levels of stress and anxiety continue for a long time, fuher problems may develop.

text:
being a victim of rape/sexual assault one of the things that i've dealt with is the desire to feel sensual but not feeling safe to be seen in that way. it's caused a lot of issues in my everyday life that takes a lot of work to overcome.
society teaches us that if we are covered up we won't be attractive or bring attention to ourselves and that'll protect us. that if they don't see it they won't desire it. 
in fact one of the first questions i was asked after the first assault was "what did you have on?" and "didn't you fight back?" for years i covered myself in an effort to protect myself and it still happened again. 
then i realized it wasn't me! it's never been my fault. and well, i'm sick of society conditioning us to feel this way and making victims feel like we asked for it. 
the truth is some people are scum and scummy people do scummy shit. nobody asks to be assaulted and no one deserves it. and for all the "strong" people that think it's as easy as fighting back you've obviously never come face to face with a crazy man thats twice as strong as you are.
 for all my survivors, i admire you, i hear you and i love you. i pray that you find love and comfort in knowing you are not alone and it has never been your fault. i pray one day you are able to peel the layers off and uncover yourself.
i pray that one day we all know pleasure is our birthright. 
you are beautiful.
you are safe to be seen. 
you are worthy. 
i love you ğŸ’™ğŸ’š
#metoo #worthy #mystory #stay #thriving #awareness #rapeculture

when i was in college i used to go home every night and fantasize about all the different ways i could kill myself.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
::â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
i was in so much emotional pain but no one ever knew it. i was on the honor roll, i had a job, friends and a boyfriend. i was outgoing an ambitious. what did i have to complain about? i wasnâ€™t hungry i  wasnâ€™t homeless.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
::â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
i tried to convince myself that it was all in my head, that i was making too big a deal of everything. i thought i was weak because i couldnâ€™t get over being raped at 17. i was drowning in shame because i believed it was my fault and i couldnâ€™t bear to tell anyone. so for me the only logical resolution was to die.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
::â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
when i look at this picture i am so happy that i made the decision to start my healing journey instead of the other option. it wouldâ€™ve been a waste to miss out on all that i have to offer this world.â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €

text:
"all falls down" by #kanyewest and #syleenajohnson
.
listen, i know he's not a very well liked dude at the moment. he's said some dumb stuff. but goddamn if i don't love his music. the question becomes at what point do we separate the art from the artist? which given everything that has happened this year with the metoo movement (which is a good thing), more and more of my favorite artists in movies and music have this shadow over them. kevin spacey was one of my favorite actors but now i have a hard time watching any of his work knowing he was a bad person. harvey weinstein is a disgusting monster, but he produced, hell discovered and created, some of the greatest movies ever made.
so do we have to ignore these great works because the men who made them were awful people? i don't know.
.

âœ¨
this, ladies and gentleman, is what it looks like to embody the change one seeks to see in the world around them. .
âœ¨

text:
i just lost 8lbs, i feel so much better, i really hope this is just the beginning. i've struggled with my weight my whole life; while refusing to be what people in the creative industries/men wanted me to be...i am not an object, i am a person! so the more i know i'm loved and loveable, i feel liberated to not have to hide myself. i know the man i love; loves me as i am, so i feel safe to climb out from underneath something that hid me. nobody wants to be loved just for their body. my technique is not a great life technique, i must admit, but i learned very quickly that people judge you upon the way you look, not upon your heart, not upon your character, i wanted to be loved for me in all my fullness. there is a lot of fullness to love. i'm not known for my figure, i'm known for my character and the way i make people feel. so i suppose i've felt safe enough to lose a little weight and get(as you can imagine) more counselling. i'm never going to be small, i'm not really built like that, but it's nice to feel good in my own skin without making it about receiving love and being an object. i am a woman not a fantasy. sorry for the over share but we all have unconscious emotions that drive our behaviour and i thought i'd be honest about some of mine!

#imnotanobjectimawoman #metoo  #weightlossjourney #dieting #loseweight #irememberwhoiam #imawomannotafantasy

text:

last summer i had a guest who slammed a brick on the head of another boy when he was still a minor, causing permanent brain damage to the victim and sending my guest to youth detention incl. forced psychiatric treatment. he used to cut his arms with razorblades (see photo elsewhere on my profile).
another guest was a physician who regularly binges on and injects herself with an anaesthetic drug (photo) probably in order to self-medicate her pain. she was bullied and sexually harassed for many years in the hospital where she used to work...
.

.

text:
aÃ±o nuevo 2012 me reuni con mi grupo de amigos de colegio, un grupo de mas de 10 personas donde yo soy la unica mujer. personalmente ellos siempre me dieron la confianza para sentirme segura entre ellos y asi mismo yo nunca les di razones para desconfiar de mi. salimos y como cualquiera en aÃ±o nuevo bebimos hasta el amanecer. 10 hombres y una mujer bebiendo hasta el amanecer. me diverti? si!. bebi? si!. algunos terminaron durmiendo? si!. me violaron? no!.
es aqui donde parte la humanidad y educacion de cada uno, de lo que aprende uno afuera de su casa porque aunque tu sepas lo que es el abuso y lo que puedes hacer como hombre y en grupo a una mujer, no lo haces.
yo no tuve suerte, ellos se educaron y nunca intentaron hacerme algo malo, por el contrario, siempre fueron como mis hermanos mayores tratandome de la mejor manera porque yo era la unica mujer del grupo. aun con los juegos bruscos que teniamos, siempre hubo respeto. yo siempre voy a estar agradecida por el cariÃ±o que siempre nos hemos tenido aun con lo poco que hablamos actualmente, siempre los tengo en mi corazon y pensamientos.
no podemos excusar a un violador(o grupo de violadores) solo porque "es joven, no sabe lo que hace". y mucho menos, podemos culpar a la victima cuando ella fue la que fue abusada hasta el punto de la convulsion y casi muerte. dejemos de culpar a las victimas por salir solas, por como se visten, por tomar o no tomar. todos somos libres de hacer cualquiera de esas cosas. tratemos a los culpables por lo que son. violadores. y sobre todo, eduquemonos en el area de consentimiento. si ella dice que no. es no. y si esta tan intoxicada como para no saber lo que esta diciendo. es no. no nos convirtamos en complices de estos crimenes.

text:
do you have a hard time just being? âœ¨â£
â£
are your thoughts always focused on the future, the goals, the dreams, or even worrying about whatâ€™s to come? â£
â£
i totally get it, i was that person... i still battle that person. i know what itâ€™s like to constantly be pushing, pulling, striving,  charging, grasping for the future, the goals, the dreams and the accomplishments. â£
â£
i also know how effing exhausting it is. i thought that it was the way successful people lived. how they became successful. â£
â£
but as i started to study the successful people i looked up to there was a common theme. they all spoke of knowing when to slow down. they spoke of being present. they spoke of mindfulness. they spoke of stillness. they spoke of clarity. even if they werenâ€™t fully present while gaining all of their success, they all spoke of how they would have focused more on that if they could go back. thatâ€™s how i feel now. â£
â£
i wanted that. i needed that. â£
so thatâ€™s the journey iâ€™ve been embarking on. for over a year, peeling back layers of the built up stress, worry, fear, anger...and discovering me. whatâ€™s crazy is i feel that iâ€™m just getting started. iâ€™m opening up channels of my being i didnâ€™t even know existed. iâ€™m feeling things i didnâ€™t know were possible. and iâ€™m being in ways i always dreamt of. slowly but surely. â£
â£
am i still working? hell yes. just smarter.â£
am i still setting goals? duh, but with more intention for the now. â£
â£
i want you to know that if your goals are all you focus on, instead of the present moment and you create this pattern. then no matter what you achieve in the future, the future will always look better. you will never be satisfied no matter how successful you become. and i promise thatâ€™s no way to live. â£
â£
i coach on this with my clients but one tip on focusing more on the present and living in the now, is to focus on gratitude in every moment. when you are grateful for the now, no matter how big or small, it keeps you in the present moment and keeps your spirit out of conflict. carrying around a gratitude journal or a note in your phone for when you need to get yourself in check is a good idea. â£
â£

2ï¸âƒ£naomi osaka of japan cries as @serenawilliams of the usa comforts her after the crowd booed during the trophy ceremony at the 2018 #usopen. osaka defeated williams in the final round of the competition.

3ï¸âƒ£president donald #trump shakes hands with #northkoreaâ€™s kim jong un at the capella hotel on sentosa island in singapore

4ï¸âƒ£saleh hassan al-faqeh holds the hand of his four-month-old daughter, hajar, who died at the malnutrition ward of al-sabeen hospital in #yemen

5ï¸âƒ£victims and others look on as rachael denhollander speaks at the sentencing hearing for #larrynassar, a former team usa #gymnastics doctor who pleaded guilty in november 2017 to sexual assault charges

6ï¸âƒ£ film producer #harveyweinstein arrives at manhattan criminal court in new york. weinstein was one of the first men accused of sexual misconduct in the #metoo movement.

7ï¸âƒ£ two #immigrant families separated at the border relax after being reunited in el paso, texas.

8ï¸âƒ£flowers and other items have been left as memorials outside the #treeoflife after a mass shooting at the synagogue that killed 11

9ï¸âƒ£icebergs float in a fjord in greenland. according to the 2018 arctic report card, as global temperatures rise, the greenland ice sheet is slowly melting. #globalwarming #climatechange

a sexualidade feminina era vista como uma forÃ§a a ser controlada e reprimida, pois sÃ³ os desejos sexuais dos homens importavam. que natureza masculina Ã© essa que tanto gosta de assediar, estrupar e matar? que sociedade Ã© essa que tanto odeia mulheres livres e empoderadas?

nossas antepassadas sofreram por sÃ©culos essa opressÃ£o, porque eram domesticadas e nÃ£o tinham voz. se uma mulher ousasse amar e se casar com alguÃ©m que nÃ£o fosse escolhido pela famÃ­lia, e se atravesse a estudar e trabalhar, poderia ser agredida ou morta, sem ninguÃ©m questionar.

joÃ£o dos infernos simboliza a forÃ§a do patriarcado, homens poderosos que abusam da vulnerabilidade de pessoas, que as manipulam para satisfazer seus desejos.

quando um homem â€œpoderosoâ€, â€œ lÃ­der espiritualistaâ€, Ã© o agressor, vemos que Ã© mais complicado o processo da denÃºncia. o risco de uma mulher ser ameaÃ§ada de morte triplica.

espero que, um dia, nÃ£o tenham medo de denunciar seus agressores, que nÃ£o se importem com que a sociedade irÃ¡ dizer, que estejam protegidas pelo estado e por pessoas queridas, que nÃ£o sejam questionadas e tenham suas vidas viradas do avesso - para confirmar se sÃ£o â€œsantasâ€ ou â€œputasâ€. minha solidariedade Ã s mulheres que superaram o medo e que tiveram coragem de denunciar.

text:
i'm mad to be told: be careful, try to go with one of your friends, tell your father to go look for you with the car, keep talking to me on the phone in case someone bothers you ... i'm haract. in this life i should not be brave, nor live with fear, i should have the freedom to go as i please at the time i want and with whom i want.

because a precious hello is not a praise, it is a sign of danger, because your desire to seek pleasure is not mine, i want to get to my house alive and without having to run because i feel watched.

what's the difference if i wear a skirt or jeans? what difference does it make if i'm blond or brown? ... what's the matter, i'm still a person and your shitty compliments are nothing but shit, so if you think that by saying:, and that ass that does not pass hungry or dame to you mobile guapa you think you're doing me a favor, go away, seriously, you do not do anybody any good, you just get me to be afraid of you.

i am not a toy, i do not need your protection or your help, that being a man does not mean that you are better. being a man does not make you braver even a little bit.

when they tell you to be a man when you are afraid, send them for a walk, because i am a woman and i am more brave than any man in this world, i leave his street and despite having fear, i continue to live.

my body is only mine, or i choose if i want to teach it and i choose who. you are nobody to judge me.

if i want to go to 1am in a miniskirt, i'm not asking you to scream at me, if i'm a little drunk i'm not giving you the opportunity to abuse me, if i'm covered i'm not telling you to tell me i'm boring. .. just leave me alone.

and what is love? love is beautiful, and beautiful does not mean: darling, hold on a little, or, love, who are you going out with? uyuyuy give me your phone that i see you very happy talking to your "friends". love is not violent, love does not leave scratches on your skin, love does not eat you inside ... love does not force you to go further, love does not scream or hit you, does not control you or you obliges, love makes you fly, what a pity that some make that metaphor a reality. (continued in the comments)

text:
what if acts of service went viral instead of booty pics? ğŸ”ºï¸fyi, i know this pic doesn't work for the ig algorithm.ğŸ”» booty pic: 1 million shares, viralğŸ’ƒğŸ’ƒğŸ’ƒ act of service: 7 likes, crickets ğŸ¦—ğŸ¦—ğŸ¦—ğŸ¦— conclusion: wtf!?!?!?ğŸ¤·â€â™‚ï¸ğŸ¤”ğŸ¤” why does a pic of some girl or guy's ass or abs produce countless positive replies and shares. however pics of "acts of service" are scrutinized and usually disregarded. people ask:

why are they showing the pic & trying to get praise?

text:
i wanted to be a flight attendant ğŸ‘©â€âœˆï¸ growing up, it was the only career/job i thought would help me escape my family, my childhood. i wanted to forget the things i saw, the things that happened at the hands of my family. the emotional, physical and verbal abuse. 
i remember quietly filling out the paperwork to be a flight attendant after my at the time boyfriend broke my heart in a way that can never be forgotten, who sleeps with your own cousin? only an asshole could!

i thought that at that time that was the hardest life would be but the truth is that it only got worse. i found out that life got harder, more complicated, that people always hurt you, trust was easily broken. 
i was sexually assaulted at 17 years old by a male friend and my life forever would be changed, i got pregnant and never made it to be a flight attendant. instead i became a mom. 
my life has been one hell after the other so i decided to write recently, i want to pour my pain, anger and every other emotion i feel on paper for the world to read but iâ€™m scared, iâ€™m anxious that i will fail. 
what if i suck? what if no one likes what i write? do i want to deal with another disappointment? 
any advice?

i thought that at that time that was the hardest life would be but the truth is that it only got worse. i found out that life got harder, more complicated, that people always hurt you, trust was easily broken. 
i was sexually assaulted at 17 years old by a male friend and my life forever would be changed, i got pregt and never made it to be a flight attendant. instead i became a mom.

text: miriam hopkins died of a heart attack on october 9, 1972 in new york city; she had been in town for a rare screening of the story of temple drake (1933) at moma. she was born ellen miriam hopkins on october 18, 1902 in savannah, georgia. sheÂ moved with her mother to syracuse, new york after her parents separated. she first appeared on broadway as a performer in the music box revue of 1921. she was then cast in several broadway productions through the 1920s including an american tragedy, the gardenÂ of eden, & excess baggage which were all later adapted into motion pictures without her. paramount pictures signed her to a contract in 1930 while she continued to act on broadway. her 1st feature length talkie was fast and loose (1930); she had previouslyÂ appeared in a talkie short, the home girl (1928). she was the favorite actress of several of paramount's finest directors like ernst lubitsch & rouben mamoulian. she left paramount in 1934 & appeared in screwball comedies and romantic dramas for rko & samuel goldwyn for the rest of the 1930s. she signed a contract with warner brothers in 1939 & made a couple of films with her on/off-screen nemesis bette davis--the old maid (1939) & old acquaintance (1943). she returned to broadway when film offersÂ declined in the 1940s, but she returned for 2 excellent william wyler films: the heiress (1949) & the children's hour (1961). throughout the 1950s and 1960s, she also appeared in such television shows as route 66, the outer limits, & lux video theatre. she was nominated once for an academy award for best actress: becky sharp (1935). she was an intelligent, well read person in private life & was a lifelong supporter of the democratic party (although she had brief conservative periods). she married 4 times,Â most famously to director anatole litvak; she also adopted her son michael in 1932 while she was a singleton. this portrait of fredric march, gary cooper, & her was for ernst lubitsch's adaptation of noÃ«l coward's design for living (1933). #miriamhopkinsÂ #travisbanton #fredricmarch #garycooper #ernstlubitsch  #noÃ«lcoward #designforliving #paramountpictures #academyawardnominee #precode #democrat #gownsbytravisbanton

text:
here's what i know:  there is a flip side to everything. 
a counter thought, feeling and belief for every thought, feeling and belief we have. 
and i know that while the holiday season, wrapping up the end of the year and starting a new year is filled with peace, joy and excitement for many, it can be a time of sadness, hopelessness and grief for others.
.

we have to talk about it.
.

according to mentalhealth.net up to 15% of the adult population and up to 25% of adolescents will experience depression at some point.
.

depression is real.  and it may not look like it's portrayed in the movies.  it may look like everything is perfectly okay on the outside and someone can still be in deep despair and turmoil on the inside.
.

the good thing is that depression is treatable. 
be it through talk therapy, medication, nutrition, exercise, meditation, aromatherapy or many other modalities. 
yet for any of these to work, we need to be able to let someone know how we're really feeling. 
that can be a scary first step, but it's necessary.
.

one of the quickest ways to begin to shift from depression is to focus on what you're grateful for. 
thoughts become feelings which become beliefs and we have the power to intercept our depressed thoughts and replace them with thoughts of gratitude. it's not the whole solution, but it can definitely be a part of your support plan.
.

brain science confirms an attitude of grattitude can actually change our mood.  so give it a try.  make a habit of listing what you're gratefiul for. not just the big stuff, but the itty bitty stuff too.
.

and please get help. understand that there is no shame in feeling your feelings, even depression. 
let someone know.
whether you reach out to a friend, family member, someone at your place of worship, a life coach, therapist, counselor, teacher, doctor, helpline or other....let help in.
.

thankfully, you don't have to suffer with depression alone.
.

will you reach out today?  either to get support or give support or just to check in and hold space for someone?
let's talk about it.
.
ğŸ’œ
.
*if you are feeling depressed and/or suicidal call 91(usa) or google search a hotline number in your area.

did you know? 
eka pÄda rÄjakapotasana- (pigeon pose) rÄjakapota meaning king of pigeons. 
stretches the quadriceps, hip flexors, abdomen, thorax, ankles, groin, psoas (large muscles that starts at the sides of your lumbar& runs down to your groin). this asana has many variations, for beginners-you can start in a chair! yes a chair!!! of course, this one depicted in the picture is appropriate for intermediate, and of course advanced, taking this asana straight into king pigeon, for the ultimate hip opener! 
our hips carry all kinds of baggage, since our very first hurt, loss, broken heart, it all adds up and as we continue to pile shit into them, we begin creating arthritis, lower back pain-shooting down the mega to the feet, causing even more troubles, like hip replacements, that is why it is essential to open them up and release all the stagnation in them! â€œi have injuries and i am not flexible!â€ â€œcan i still do pigeon pose if youâ€™ve already had a hip
replacement?â€ yes, yes and yes!! there is not one person i know, who has not moved in a long time who is flexible lol, time heals all things and that includes your body, mind and eventually soul! 
remember, as long as your doctor is on board, & believe me doctors now see how yoga benefits the body! start with the chair & work your way up! if you now sure look for my youtube video!! blessings to all ğŸ¥°ğŸ™ŒğŸ•‰ğŸ’Ÿ @@@@@@@

text:
how to cultivate a tribe around your brand ğŸ’«
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
to cultivate a tribe around your brand that embodies who you are and what you stand for, you can do the following things:
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
1. start your own fb community - this is a great way to start getting awareness around your brand and offer and really speak directly to your ideal clients and followers (like i am doing for you all right now)
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
2. start a blog - most of you in here are bloggers or beginning your own blog. congrats on those who are beginning the journey! a blog is a great way to get out there and start creating a community around your brand. i suggest starting with a niche on your blog (i.e. fitness, fashion, entrepreneurship, business, travel, food etc.). that way you can become known for that specific thing and then expand on that solid foundation.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
3. do small things for your followers and clients - sometimes itâ€™s the little things that make the biggest impact online. the brands that i remember are the ones that give a special, personalized note in their packages. i do this by doing small giveaways in my ig stories (if you havenâ€™t looked there, be sure you do)! i will also be doing this for my p2p students :)
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
4. give value after value - this one never gets old. think about how you can give value to your followers and clients. will this leave them better than when they first read the post? if the answer is yes, you are one step closer to looking at your potential client!
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
5. create a movement - use a specific hashtag to create a movement around your brand that is specific to your brand. if you are a blogger this could look like #abmlifeisbeautiful or #metoo for example, are two hashtags that literally created a movement.
â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €â €
there are many more tidbits on how to create that true #vibetribe, but the most important is be so authentically you that no one can touch you and your vibe tribe. no one can f*ck with your vibration ğŸ’¯
